Manchester United can expect competition from Spanish giants Barcelona and Real Madrid for Aston Villa captain Jack Grealish this summer, claims The Sun. Grealish is expected to be one of the most in-demand English players this summer after United made him their top transfer target ahead of Leicester’s James Maddison. The 24-year-old is spearheading Villa’s bid to beat the drop this season and is playing his way into Gareth Southgate’s England plans for Euro 2020. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network United were considered the only club in for Grealish but now it is understood Barcelona and Madrid have entered the race for his signature. Barcelona and Madrid are expected to be busy in the summer transfer window and Grealish has emerged on their radar.